A- Pours a semi-hazy medium amber color with a 3/4 inch off-white head that retains well before becoming a thin ring around the edge of the glass and a large side patch of bubbly surface foam.  Resilient lacing leaves large clots behind.
S- Great classic mosaic hop nose with a nice cereal grain malt sweetness to support it.  
T- Flavor doesn't quite live up to the nose.  The hop character is decent but a bit limp and overshadowed by the malt presence.  Bitterness is on the lower end of the spectrum.  Very easy to drink, just not super vibrant.
M- Somewhat dry and a bit sharp from the hops.  Medium carbonation and a body leaning toward the lighter side.
O- A solid IPA but not one that I would actively seek out again. 779 charactersImmortale25, Apr 29, 2017
