4.22/5  rDev -4.5%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Traded for this a few months ago and also had a sip of this on the Other Half line fairly recently. The ratings for this were really high on here and I'm pretty sure that I'm spoiled by all of the outstanding IPA's that have risen out of nowhere the last few years here in the northeast as I didn't think that this beer was amazing, like so many others on here. This was great and balance but it felt just a bit too light to come across as an IPA...
Great pour to this as the beer had a cloudy, goldenrod hue to it, a massive head full of life, and tons of soapy lacing that slid down the side of my pint glass. Lots of grapefruit and Mosaic sweetness in the nose with a hint of elderflower, as the juice from the blueberry and pineapple tang came through in the taste. Lots of sweet malt, dank resin, and a light carbonation all worked together to give this good depth as the citrus, stone fruit, and berry fruit all melded together quite nicely. 
The alcohol was just right as this almost felt like a Pale Ale rather than an IPA. Plenty of balance here thanks to the generous amount of malt with hardly any bitterness or burn from the hop. This was juicy, slick, and left just a hint of resin once it was all down. A solid IPA that's neither East nor West coast - hopheads and fans of fruit beers would be wise to get their hands on this. Just like Texas, this is an IPA not worth messing with! 1,398 charactersJerzDevl2000, Jul 29, 2016
