Look- Clear yellow orange with a white bubbly head.  Looks a bit light in the malt character.
Smell- big tropical fruit bouquet, huge guava and passionfruit notes, mango, kiwi, sweet eucalyptus honey, apricot.
Taste- a bit grassy and grainy at first as the Pilsner malts stand up, but the honey sweetness amplifies the floral hop character.  More fruity than bitter.
Feel- a bit fizzy, smooth and refreshing.
Overall- a great beer.  One of the best single IPAs I've had.  Great single hop/single malt brew.  Beauty in the simplicity. 566 charactersSaisonRichBiere, Mar 23, 2015
